1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,002
[Marcus] <i>I'm still angry with your son.</i>

2
00:00:03,086 --> 00:00:06,881
I don't know how I can forgive him
after what he did to my father.

3
00:00:07,424 --> 00:00:09,801
<i>I know I should be grateful to him.</i>

4
00:00:09,884 --> 00:00:11,720
<i>Because he saved my life.</i>

5
00:00:11,803 --> 00:00:13,012
[Teresa] <i>It just so happened</i>

6
00:00:13,096 --> 00:00:15,598
<i>that it was the mission</i>
<i>he was given at the time.</i>

7
00:00:15,682 --> 00:00:18,393
<i>However, he suspects</i>
<i>that they were sabotaged,</i>

8
00:00:18,476 --> 00:00:19,894
<i>which is why it got messed up.</i>

9
00:00:19,978 --> 00:00:21,354
[Norhana] <i>Jamilah!</i>

10
00:00:22,188 --> 00:00:24,774
[Azuelo, in English] I would like
to personally commend

11
00:00:24,858 --> 00:00:26,901
the new Task Force Alpha.

12
00:00:27,527 --> 00:00:28,611
[crowd cheering, applauding]

13
00:00:28,695 --> 00:00:31,114
Our priority is the safety of civilians.

14
00:00:31,197 --> 00:00:33,575
- [gunshot]
- [crowd clamoring]

15
00:00:33,658 --> 00:00:34,701
[gunshot]

16
00:00:34,784 --> 00:00:37,245
[crowd clamoring]

17
00:00:38,621 --> 00:00:41,541
[Marcus] <i>Search the area.</i>
<i>Look for evidence.</i>

18
00:00:41,624 --> 00:00:43,293
<i>Shell casings, anything.</i>

19
00:00:44,377 --> 00:00:45,795
[grunts]

20
00:00:46,463 --> 00:00:48,339
[grunting and groaning]

21
00:00:48,423 --> 00:00:49,716
[grunts]

22
00:00:49,799 --> 00:00:51,801
[grunting]

23
00:00:56,014 --> 00:00:59,017
- [Usman] <i>Montes, what are you doing?</i>
- Tying my shoes.

24
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:01,686
Protect the remaining suspect
in the hospital.

25
00:01:01,770 --> 00:01:02,771
[Felix] <i>I'll give you a choice.</i>

26
00:01:02,854 --> 00:01:06,441
Either I kill your mother or…

27
00:01:06,524 --> 00:01:08,068
you'll kill yourself.

28
00:01:08,568 --> 00:01:09,736
- [gunshot]
- [people screaming]

29
00:01:09,819 --> 00:01:11,529
[Azuelo] Those crooks
were supposed to lead us

30
00:01:11,613 --> 00:01:15,950
to their supplier
of high-powered firearms!

31
00:01:16,034 --> 00:01:18,578
<i>You're telling me their brother,</i>
<i>the only surviving suspect,</i>

32
00:01:18,661 --> 00:01:20,121
<i>committed suicide?!</i>

33
00:01:20,663 --> 00:01:21,790
[Montes] <i>The sniper left this behind.</i>

34
00:01:21,873 --> 00:01:23,458
[Ahmad] <i>This isn't a random incident.</i>

35
00:01:23,541 --> 00:01:25,585
<i>Someone is definitely</i>
<i>pulling the strings here.</i>

36
00:01:25,668 --> 00:01:27,128
This is a destabilization attempt.

37
00:01:31,174 --> 00:01:34,427
[mysterious theme music playing]

38
00:01:46,815 --> 00:01:51,236
[somber music playing]

39
00:01:51,319 --> 00:01:53,988
[panting]

40
00:01:54,072 --> 00:01:55,198
[knock on door]

41
00:01:57,242 --> 00:01:58,576
[knock on door]

42
00:02:00,411 --> 00:02:01,246
Madam.

43
00:02:02,997 --> 00:02:05,125
[pensive music playing]

44
00:02:07,293 --> 00:02:08,294
[door clicks shut]

45
00:02:08,878 --> 00:02:10,797
- What's that?
- I've cleaned it up.

46
00:02:12,006 --> 00:02:14,551
Even the youngest brother… is dead.

47
00:02:16,845 --> 00:02:19,806
Uh, he committed "suicide".

48
00:02:21,516 --> 00:02:24,227
- So we don't have any more problems.
- No, no. [exhales]

49
00:02:24,310 --> 00:02:25,353
There's already a lot on my plate.

50
00:02:25,436 --> 00:02:26,771
I don't need to know that.

51
00:02:26,855 --> 00:02:28,439
[pensive music playing]

52
00:02:28,523 --> 00:02:30,024
[sighs] Hold on.

53
00:02:31,109 --> 00:02:32,318
I don't understand you.

54
00:02:33,528 --> 00:02:36,489
You told me before
that you wanted to know everything.

55
00:02:37,782 --> 00:02:41,077
You got mad at me when I didn't tell you
I killed Oliver and the others.

56
00:02:45,331 --> 00:02:49,419
And now I update you with everything I do,

57
00:02:49,502 --> 00:02:50,712
and you tell me

58
00:02:51,379 --> 00:02:53,047
you don't want to know?

59
00:02:53,923 --> 00:02:54,924
[in English] Shut up!

60
00:02:55,466 --> 00:02:57,051
- [in English] Shut up!
- Whoa.

61
00:02:57,135 --> 00:02:58,553
[in English] Get out of my face!

62
00:03:00,722 --> 00:03:01,848
[in English] Get out!

63
00:03:04,142 --> 00:03:06,352
I'm just doing my job, Lara.

64
00:03:07,979 --> 00:03:11,608
Don't forget how important our mission is.

65
00:03:15,153 --> 00:03:16,404
[whispers in English] Get out.

66
00:03:17,071 --> 00:03:18,615
[sharp inhale]

67
00:03:18,698 --> 00:03:22,911
[pensive music continues]

68
00:03:22,994 --> 00:03:24,162
[music fades]

69
00:03:24,245 --> 00:03:25,538
[footsteps retreating]

70
00:03:25,622 --> 00:03:26,998
[door clicks open and shut]

71
00:03:28,499 --> 00:03:31,336
[morose music playing]

72
00:03:31,419 --> 00:03:32,378
[exhales forcefully]

73
00:03:33,671 --> 00:03:39,093
[breathing heavily]

74
00:03:43,223 --> 00:03:46,142
[traffic noise]

75
00:03:46,226 --> 00:03:48,186
[metal door, lock clattering]

76
00:03:50,271 --> 00:03:52,440
[tense music playing]

77
00:03:56,861 --> 00:03:57,862
What do you know about these?

78
00:04:02,992 --> 00:04:04,369
[Marcus] What?

79
00:04:04,452 --> 00:04:05,578
Speak up!

80
00:04:12,085 --> 00:04:14,295
Datu Rahman,
a lot of people have already died.

81
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:17,006
And many more could die

82
00:04:17,090 --> 00:04:19,384
if you refuse to tell the truth.

83
00:04:19,884 --> 00:04:22,971
I thought you wanted to give justice
to your community?

84
00:04:23,054 --> 00:04:25,139
Datu Rahman, this is your chance.

85
00:04:25,682 --> 00:04:28,601
This is it. Tell me what you know!

86
00:04:31,145 --> 00:04:34,691
[somber music playing]

87
00:04:37,151 --> 00:04:38,069
Nothing.

88
00:04:42,490 --> 00:04:46,369
They were using RPG!
The criminals were using an RPG.

89
00:04:46,452 --> 00:04:48,329
They were using RPG.

90
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:52,083
How? How could they have such a weapon?

91
00:04:54,168 --> 00:04:55,628
I've told you already.

92
00:04:56,838 --> 00:04:58,881
I don't have anything to do with that!

93
00:04:59,382 --> 00:05:01,634
I'm not a part of the syndicate!

94
00:05:01,718 --> 00:05:03,886
[music intensifies]

95
00:05:03,970 --> 00:05:04,846
How about this?

96
00:05:06,848 --> 00:05:08,516
These three brothers.

97
00:05:09,309 --> 00:05:10,393
Do you know them?

98
00:05:15,481 --> 00:05:18,067
- No.
- Don't try to fool me.

99
00:05:19,485 --> 00:05:21,446
I know the truth, Datu Rahman.

100
00:05:21,529 --> 00:05:25,700
I know you were involved
on how they got the weapons.

101
00:05:27,243 --> 00:05:28,661
Are they the ones who set you up?

102
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:31,205
Huh? Are they?

103
00:05:31,289 --> 00:05:32,915
[music subdues]

104
00:05:32,999 --> 00:05:34,959
I said I don't know anything.

105
00:05:35,918 --> 00:05:38,504
You can elicit information all you want,

106
00:05:38,588 --> 00:05:40,757
torture me all you want,

107
00:05:41,299 --> 00:05:42,633
or even kill me.

108
00:05:43,301 --> 00:05:48,056
I have nothing to say
because I don't know anything!

109
00:05:48,723 --> 00:05:49,891
‪[music intensifies]

110
00:06:03,613 --> 00:06:05,239
[door clicks open, shut]

111
00:06:05,323 --> 00:06:07,617
[lock clattering]

112
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:09,535
‪[tense music playing]

113
00:06:23,257 --> 00:06:27,220
[Datu Rahman] <i>My silence</i>
<i>will protect my children.</i>

114
00:06:28,429 --> 00:06:31,057
<i>You can't know the truth.</i>

115
00:06:31,140 --> 00:06:31,974
‪[music intensifies]

116
00:06:35,686 --> 00:06:36,938
[music fades]

117
00:06:37,021 --> 00:06:43,986
[morose music playing]

118
00:06:49,492 --> 00:06:52,537
[unsettling music playing]

119
00:06:57,708 --> 00:06:59,043
[dramatic sting]

120
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:08,678
- Jalil.
- Jamilah.

121
00:07:10,304 --> 00:07:11,889
I'm glad you're safe.

122
00:07:13,141 --> 00:07:15,685
[sentimental music playing]

123
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:19,272
[Jamilah moans]

124
00:07:20,815 --> 00:07:22,275
What happened to you?

125
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:27,196
Why did you disappear and…
why are you with Task Force Alpha?

126
00:07:30,366 --> 00:07:31,492
Come here.

127
00:07:33,244 --> 00:07:36,414
Jamilah. It's hard to explain.

128
00:07:37,415 --> 00:07:39,459
But I'm already inside SID.

129
00:07:40,001 --> 00:07:41,419
- What?!
- I infiltrated

130
00:07:41,502 --> 00:07:44,672
Marcus Reyes' group to find out the truth.

131
00:07:44,755 --> 00:07:48,050
- To find father.
- But how?!

132
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:50,303
- Jalil, that's too dangerous!
- [tense music playing]

133
00:07:50,386 --> 00:07:53,431
Jamilah, I know.
But what matters is I'm already inside.

134
00:07:53,514 --> 00:07:55,099
The people I'm up against,

135
00:07:55,183 --> 00:08:00,062
whoever is behind all of this,
they're powerful.

136
00:08:02,106 --> 00:08:04,150
- [rapid gunfire]
- [people clamoring]

137
00:08:04,859 --> 00:08:06,986
- [rapid gunfire]
- [people clamoring]

138
00:08:07,653 --> 00:08:08,821
[girl] Papa!

139
00:08:08,905 --> 00:08:10,656
[woman] Come here! Let's hide!

140
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:16,496
- [rapid gunfire]
- [people clamoring]

141
00:08:17,955 --> 00:08:21,501
[suspenseful music playing]

142
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:25,713
And only people in the agency
could do this to father.

143
00:08:25,796 --> 00:08:27,298
So I know…

144
00:08:27,381 --> 00:08:29,926
Jamilah, I know I'm on the right track.

145
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:33,471
Jalil, I don't want you to get hurt.

146
00:08:35,056 --> 00:08:39,060
But I feel like
we're getting closer to Father.

147
00:08:39,143 --> 00:08:42,146
Jamilah, I don't want you
to get hurt either.

148
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:43,648
But you're not listening.

149
00:08:43,731 --> 00:08:47,026
Why did you apply at that hospital?
Why are you there?

150
00:08:48,653 --> 00:08:50,780
Because I know I can help you.

151
00:08:50,863 --> 00:08:54,534
- [scoffs]
- I'm getting closer to Dr. Teresa.

152
00:08:54,617 --> 00:08:58,287
And I know Marcus Reyes
is doing everything

153
00:08:58,371 --> 00:09:00,623
to find out what really happened
on the island.

154
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:06,712
Jalil, he believes someone sabotaged them.

155
00:09:08,005 --> 00:09:10,675
I know you're against
what I'm doing, Jalil,

156
00:09:11,926 --> 00:09:13,886
but if you let me,

157
00:09:14,387 --> 00:09:16,722
I can help you a lot.

158
00:09:18,140 --> 00:09:19,183
[Jamilah sobs]

159
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:23,271
Jalil, our lives are so complicated now.

160
00:09:25,648 --> 00:09:29,902
I want to do everything
to end all of this.

161
00:09:30,611 --> 00:09:34,574
To bring our lives back to how they were.
Our peaceful lives.

162
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:38,160
[Jamilah cries] Jalil…

163
00:09:38,244 --> 00:09:40,663
Why are they doing this to us?

164
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:43,916
Why does this have to happen?

165
00:09:46,002 --> 00:09:48,713
[sobs] Jalil, I want to go back
to the island.

166
00:09:48,796 --> 00:09:50,298
[somber music playing]

167
00:09:50,381 --> 00:09:52,091
- [Jamilah sobs]
- That's what I want too.

168
00:09:53,342 --> 00:09:55,011
And I promise you…

169
00:09:58,806 --> 00:10:00,474
we'll go back to the island…

170
00:10:01,976 --> 00:10:03,227
with Father.

171
00:10:05,271 --> 00:10:06,564
I hope that's still possible.

172
00:10:06,647 --> 00:10:08,232
- [sobs, cries]
- I'll do everything.

173
00:10:08,816 --> 00:10:10,735
I'll do everything to make it possible.

174
00:10:12,486 --> 00:10:14,905
I'll do it for you and Father.

175
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:18,993
[in Arabic] God willing, Jalil.

176
00:10:20,536 --> 00:10:21,996
[in Arabic] God willing.

177
00:10:22,079 --> 00:10:24,665
[somber music playing]

178
00:10:26,459 --> 00:10:27,752
[Jamilah crying, sobbing]

179
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:30,338
[in Arabic] God willing.

180
00:10:33,007 --> 00:10:34,008
[crying]

181
00:10:55,363 --> 00:10:58,908
[pensive music playing]

182
00:11:06,457 --> 00:11:10,252
Stop disappointing me.

183
00:11:23,891 --> 00:11:26,852
- [gunshot]
- [people clamoring]

184
00:11:41,784 --> 00:11:44,120
I'm just doing my job, Lara.

185
00:11:45,579 --> 00:11:49,250
Don't forget how important our mission is.

186
00:11:58,050 --> 00:12:00,177
[crickets chirping]

187
00:12:01,929 --> 00:12:06,100
[somber music playing]

188
00:12:45,014 --> 00:12:46,599
- [boy 1] <i>Come here.</i>
- [young Felix] <i>What?!</i>

189
00:12:46,682 --> 00:12:48,642
- And you're still resisting.
- I'm not doing anything to you!

190
00:12:48,726 --> 00:12:50,603
What do you mean nothing?
Just come with us!

191
00:12:50,686 --> 00:12:51,812
- What, you're brave now?
- Hey! Let me go!

192
00:12:51,896 --> 00:12:54,106
- Stop resisting.
- Let me go!

193
00:12:54,190 --> 00:12:55,357
- Please!
- Come here!

194
00:12:55,441 --> 00:12:57,067
Please, stop!

195
00:12:57,151 --> 00:12:58,736
- You're brave?!
- Move!

196
00:12:58,819 --> 00:13:00,070
[screams]

197
00:13:00,154 --> 00:13:01,280
- Come here!
- [boys laughing]

198
00:13:01,363 --> 00:13:03,741
- What! You're brave, huh!
- [grunting]

199
00:13:03,824 --> 00:13:05,284
[grunting]

200
00:13:05,367 --> 00:13:07,369
Push him! There!

201
00:13:07,453 --> 00:13:08,579
What's your problem!

202
00:13:08,662 --> 00:13:10,623
You've always been so weak!

203
00:13:10,706 --> 00:13:12,541
That's why your drunk father beats you up!

204
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:13,626
[grunting]

205
00:13:13,709 --> 00:13:14,793
Felix, so soft!

206
00:13:14,877 --> 00:13:17,713
[groaning, grunting]

207
00:13:18,964 --> 00:13:21,258
[grunting]

208
00:13:21,342 --> 00:13:23,093
- Come here!
- [grunting]

209
00:13:23,177 --> 00:13:24,345
- [boy 2 laughing]
- [boy 1] Now what?!

210
00:13:24,428 --> 00:13:25,471
[boy laughing]

211
00:13:25,554 --> 00:13:27,598
[boy] Come on! We have nothing
to gain from that crybaby.

212
00:13:27,681 --> 00:13:30,059
- [boy 1] Woo! Woo!
- [boy coughs]

213
00:13:31,727 --> 00:13:32,645
[boy 2] He's such a crybaby.

214
00:13:32,728 --> 00:13:34,522
- [spits]
- [boys laughing]

215
00:13:35,981 --> 00:13:38,901
[crying]

216
00:13:43,739 --> 00:13:47,910
[sinister music playing]

217
00:13:47,993 --> 00:13:49,578
- [man 1] It's my shot.
- [man 2] Drink up.

218
00:13:49,662 --> 00:13:50,829
- [man groaning]
- [man 2] Drink up, drink.

219
00:13:50,913 --> 00:13:53,999
Hey! Your kid got beaten up again.

220
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:55,876
- [laughs]
- Your son's too weak.

221
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:57,086
He doesn't know how to fight!

222
00:13:57,169 --> 00:13:59,421
[man] How did you raise him, anyway?

223
00:13:59,505 --> 00:14:01,465
You're all macho, while your son's weak!

224
00:14:02,132 --> 00:14:02,967
[beer bottle clinks]

225
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:04,426
[father] I'll hit you in the face!

226
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:05,719
- [table rattling]
- [dog barks]

227
00:14:05,803 --> 00:14:07,137
- Hey!
- [men laughing]

228
00:14:07,221 --> 00:14:10,099
- What did you do this time?! Huh?!
- [men launghing]

229
00:14:10,182 --> 00:14:12,268
- You're humiliating. Go home!
- [indistinct chattering]

230
00:14:12,351 --> 00:14:13,727
I'll hit you, I swear!

231
00:14:15,437 --> 00:14:16,522
[man] Come on.

232
00:14:36,125 --> 00:14:37,585
- [sighs]
- [shuffling]

233
00:14:50,931 --> 00:14:52,099
[object clangs]

234
00:14:59,023 --> 00:15:00,441
- Hey!
- [unsetting music playing]

235
00:15:00,524 --> 00:15:02,276
You can't do anything right, can you?!

236
00:15:02,359 --> 00:15:04,445
- You just keep humiliating me!
- [bottle rattling]

237
00:15:06,655 --> 00:15:08,824
What's your problem with me, Pa?

238
00:15:09,408 --> 00:15:12,661
- I never did anything bad to you!
- My problem?!

239
00:15:12,745 --> 00:15:14,788
It's you! You frustrate me so much!

240
00:15:15,664 --> 00:15:18,667
- What's with you? You humiliated me!
- [sobbing]

241
00:15:19,293 --> 00:15:21,337
You are an embarrassment to me!

242
00:15:21,420 --> 00:15:24,798
- [grunts]
- [young Felix screaming]

243
00:15:25,299 --> 00:15:27,551
[young Felix breathing rapidly]

244
00:15:27,635 --> 00:15:28,594
This is what you deserve.

245
00:15:28,677 --> 00:15:31,472
- [young Felix screaming]
- Damn you!

246
00:15:31,555 --> 00:15:33,474
[both screaming]

247
00:15:33,557 --> 00:15:35,809
- Shut up! I said, shut up!
- [music intensifies]

248
00:15:35,893 --> 00:15:37,353
- Pa!
- Shut up!

249
00:15:37,436 --> 00:15:38,687
[young Felix screaming]

250
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:40,773
- Does it hurt?
- [young Felix screaming]

251
00:15:40,856 --> 00:15:42,024
It's all your fault!

252
00:15:43,025 --> 00:15:46,570
[young Felix screaming]

253
00:15:46,654 --> 00:15:47,571
- Damn you!
- [blow lands]

254
00:15:47,655 --> 00:15:49,698
[young Felix screaming, wailing]

255
00:15:49,782 --> 00:15:51,325
You want more?! You want more?!

256
00:15:51,408 --> 00:15:53,410
- [young Felix] Pa… [wailing]
- You want more?!

257
00:15:53,494 --> 00:15:55,496
- Stop it!
- This isn't enough! Shut up!

258
00:15:55,579 --> 00:15:58,874
- Shut up!
- [cries]

259
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:02,920
- [young Felix wailing]
- [blow lands]

260
00:16:09,176 --> 00:16:10,886
[gasping, sobbing]

261
00:16:40,582 --> 00:16:41,834
[mirror shatters]

262
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:49,717
Hey! Quit staring!

263
00:16:50,467 --> 00:16:53,470
[chuckling] This is why
people laugh at you!

264
00:16:53,554 --> 00:16:54,388
[object thuds]

265
00:16:54,471 --> 00:16:55,806
See this?

266
00:16:56,849 --> 00:16:58,100
It's empty.

267
00:16:58,183 --> 00:16:59,768
Buy me another, quick!

268
00:17:00,561 --> 00:17:03,397
- [young Felix breathes deeply]
- You're not answering?

269
00:17:04,356 --> 00:17:06,525
Huh? Do you have anything to be proud of?

270
00:17:06,608 --> 00:17:08,068
You still haven't learned your lesson?

271
00:17:08,152 --> 00:17:10,029
Was all this not enough? Huh?

272
00:17:10,112 --> 00:17:11,947
Why don't you prove that you are my child?

273
00:17:12,031 --> 00:17:13,949
Fight back! Fight!

274
00:17:14,033 --> 00:17:16,493
Fight! Fight! [shouts]

275
00:17:16,577 --> 00:17:17,828
[chuckling]

276
00:17:18,954 --> 00:17:20,247
This is what I like about you.

277
00:17:21,582 --> 00:17:24,585
That's exactly it, my son.
You have to learn how to fight!

278
00:17:26,420 --> 00:17:28,672
See this? Huh?

279
00:17:29,339 --> 00:17:31,800
Want me to teach you
how to use this? It's easy!

280
00:17:32,342 --> 00:17:33,677
Like this! And this!

281
00:17:34,428 --> 00:17:37,139
Prove to me that you're not gay!

282
00:17:37,222 --> 00:17:41,435
Fight! Fight! Fight back!

283
00:17:41,518 --> 00:17:43,520
Prove that you are my son. Are you my son?

284
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:45,439
I do not have a homosexual son!

285
00:17:46,148 --> 00:17:47,649
- [father shouts]
- [flesh squelches]

286
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:49,526
[groans, coughs]

287
00:17:50,861 --> 00:17:52,071
- [knife swishes]
- Felix…

288
00:17:52,154 --> 00:17:53,864
[breathing rapidly]

289
00:17:53,947 --> 00:17:56,366
- [knife swishes]
- [shouting]

290
00:17:56,450 --> 00:17:59,411
- [knife swishing]
- [flesh squelching]

291
00:17:59,495 --> 00:18:04,833
[music intensifies]

292
00:18:07,211 --> 00:18:08,504
‪[dark brooding music playing]

293
00:18:35,364 --> 00:18:36,865
‪[intense dramatic music playing]

294
00:18:46,667 --> 00:18:49,086
- Sir, can I have some?
- You want some?

295
00:18:49,169 --> 00:18:51,338
Buy your own. Stop asking around.

296
00:18:52,131 --> 00:18:53,173
[man] Beggars, really.

297
00:18:56,301 --> 00:19:01,932
- [young Felix grunts]
- [grunting]

298
00:19:06,186 --> 00:19:07,104
- Give me that!
- [dog barking]

299
00:19:07,688 --> 00:19:09,398
[huffs]

300
00:19:09,481 --> 00:19:10,649
‪[sinister music playing]

301
00:19:33,547 --> 00:19:36,133
You killed someone for meager food?

302
00:19:44,183 --> 00:19:48,562
- [knife swishes]
- [young Felix grunts]

303
00:19:49,646 --> 00:19:52,191
[grunts, muffled speech]

304
00:19:52,274 --> 00:19:53,901
[grunting]

305
00:19:53,984 --> 00:19:55,527
- You're good, kid.
- [gulps]

306
00:19:55,611 --> 00:19:56,778
[breathing heavily]

307
00:19:56,862 --> 00:19:58,113
I like your courage.

308
00:19:58,947 --> 00:20:01,992
All you need is training and discipline.

309
00:20:03,785 --> 00:20:05,996
Come with me. I'll train you.

310
00:20:06,079 --> 00:20:10,459
[tense music playing]

311
00:20:14,254 --> 00:20:15,380
I'll keep this, okay?

312
00:20:24,473 --> 00:20:25,307
‪[young Felix sighs]

313
00:20:26,225 --> 00:20:27,768
[young Manuel] In a fight,

314
00:20:28,268 --> 00:20:30,771
it's not enough that you're brave.

315
00:20:31,563 --> 00:20:34,066
- You can't just be strong and quick.
- [tense dramatic music playing]

316
00:20:34,149 --> 00:20:35,609
You also have to use your brain.

317
00:20:36,860 --> 00:20:38,237
[in English] Observe your opponent.

318
00:20:39,279 --> 00:20:41,114
Read their movements.

319
00:20:42,783 --> 00:20:44,576
[young Felix grunting]

320
00:20:52,376 --> 00:20:54,002
[groans]

321
00:20:54,086 --> 00:20:55,879
[shouting]

322
00:20:55,963 --> 00:20:58,006
[breathing heavily]

323
00:20:58,090 --> 00:20:59,508
Don't give in to anger.

324
00:21:11,270 --> 00:21:13,105
[music turns pensive]

325
00:21:13,188 --> 00:21:15,857
But don't throw it away either.

326
00:21:15,941 --> 00:21:17,484
Your anger…

327
00:21:18,318 --> 00:21:19,861
will give you strength.

328
00:21:20,445 --> 00:21:21,446
[in English] So, use it wisely.

329
00:21:23,490 --> 00:21:25,325
Turn it into your weapon.

330
00:21:26,368 --> 00:21:29,288
If you kill for no reason,
you'll just be a criminal then.

331
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:31,206
A menace to society.

332
00:21:31,790 --> 00:21:33,667
Create a purpose.

333
00:21:33,750 --> 00:21:35,252
Do it for the country,

334
00:21:35,919 --> 00:21:38,672
for the people who cannot
defend themselves.

335
00:21:39,381 --> 00:21:43,302
[stirring music playing]

336
00:21:52,185 --> 00:21:53,395
You've already graduated.

337
00:21:54,479 --> 00:21:56,064
You'll be entering NLEA.

338
00:21:57,190 --> 00:21:59,359
You will work for me.

339
00:22:01,445 --> 00:22:04,197
[in English] Make me proud.

340
00:22:04,865 --> 00:22:07,242
[morose music playing]

341
00:22:10,370 --> 00:22:12,080
[in English] Sir! Yes, sir!

342
00:22:17,085 --> 00:22:17,919
‪[music intensifies]

343
00:22:40,233 --> 00:22:41,234
What should we do, Cuchy?

344
00:22:42,527 --> 00:22:44,237
[breathes deeply]

345
00:22:44,321 --> 00:22:45,530
Oh my.

346
00:22:47,074 --> 00:22:48,867
Madam is still pondering.

347
00:22:51,703 --> 00:22:54,247
She probably hasn't realized that…

348
00:22:55,123 --> 00:22:56,374
the General was right.

349
00:22:57,209 --> 00:22:59,669
But she can't see that yet.

350
00:23:00,378 --> 00:23:01,213
Do you get that?

351
00:23:02,255 --> 00:23:03,131
[clicks tongue]

352
00:23:03,215 --> 00:23:05,634
[unsettling music playing]

353
00:23:05,717 --> 00:23:07,594
That's why, Cuchy…

354
00:23:07,677 --> 00:23:09,596
Hmm? [Felix sniffles]

355
00:23:09,679 --> 00:23:11,723
[groans] Come here.

356
00:23:13,850 --> 00:23:15,393
You're going to help me, right?

357
00:23:16,645 --> 00:23:20,398
Right? We need to protect Lara.

358
00:23:21,775 --> 00:23:24,778
And I hope that someday…

359
00:23:25,278 --> 00:23:27,489
[sniffles, chuckles softly]

360
00:23:27,989 --> 00:23:30,367
…she'll learn to love us too.

361
00:23:30,951 --> 00:23:31,952
Right?

362
00:23:32,619 --> 00:23:33,912
[Felix chuckles softly]

363
00:23:33,995 --> 00:23:35,330
[sniffles]

364
00:23:35,413 --> 00:23:37,332
[in English] I love you, Cuchy.

365
00:23:39,584 --> 00:23:41,920
[in English] Cuchy. Kiss.

366
00:23:44,714 --> 00:23:47,134
[imam, in Arabic] God is great.

367
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:51,513
[in Arabic] God is great.

368
00:23:53,098 --> 00:23:56,143
[in Arabic] May Allah hear
those who praise Him.

369
00:23:58,019 --> 00:24:00,480
[in Arabic] God is great.

370
00:24:01,982 --> 00:24:04,359
[in Arabic] God is great.

371
00:24:06,027 --> 00:24:08,446
[in Arabic] God is great.

372
00:24:10,574 --> 00:24:13,243
[in Arabic] God is great.

373
00:24:16,079 --> 00:24:18,540
[Jalil] <i>Allah, thank You</i>

374
00:24:18,623 --> 00:24:21,501
<i>because Jamilah has been safe from danger.</i>

375
00:24:22,419 --> 00:24:24,921
[Marcus, in English] <i>Hostage clear.</i>
<i>Target secured.</i>

376
00:24:25,589 --> 00:24:28,300
[somber music playing]

377
00:24:33,263 --> 00:24:36,641
[Jalil] <i>I'm going against people</i>
<i>who are powerful.</i>

378
00:24:36,725 --> 00:24:38,476
- [gunshot]
- [people screaming]

379
00:24:42,230 --> 00:24:46,067
[Jalil] <i>But I know that nothing</i>
<i>is more powerful than You.</i>

380
00:24:46,651 --> 00:24:50,572
<i>I know that in the end,</i>
<i>justice will prevail.</i>

381
00:24:51,573 --> 00:24:53,283
<i>Please guide me.</i>

382
00:24:53,950 --> 00:24:57,495
<i>Please help me find</i>
<i>the answers to my questions.</i>

383
00:24:57,579 --> 00:24:59,831
<i>So we can finally be with our father again</i>

384
00:24:59,915 --> 00:25:03,168
<i>and return to our peaceful lives again.</i>

385
00:25:04,794 --> 00:25:08,548
[imam, in Arabic] May peace
and mercy of Allah be upon you.

386
00:25:09,257 --> 00:25:13,720
[in Arabic] May peace and mercy
of Allah be upon you.

387
00:25:14,346 --> 00:25:17,599
[serene music playing]

388
00:25:31,571 --> 00:25:36,534
[music turns thrilling]

389
00:25:53,927 --> 00:25:55,762
[Jalil] You're the Chief of Staff
of the President,

390
00:25:55,845 --> 00:25:58,515
but you're asking me
to investigate the crime syndicate.

391
00:25:58,598 --> 00:26:03,103
The increase in arms sales
has severely affected our country.

392
00:26:03,186 --> 00:26:04,479
Is that the only reason, sir?

393
00:26:04,562 --> 00:26:06,982
Or is there a deeper reason?

394
00:26:07,482 --> 00:26:09,150
[Marcus] <i>If I can't get</i>
<i>an answer from you,</i>

395
00:26:09,234 --> 00:26:11,403
- <i>I'll find out the truth in another way.</i>
- [suspenseful music playing]

396
00:26:11,486 --> 00:26:13,697
Agent Reyes filed for an official leave.

397
00:26:13,780 --> 00:26:14,781
[in English] What?

398
00:26:14,864 --> 00:26:18,285
That's why you will pair up
with Agent Angeles for now.

399
00:26:18,368 --> 00:26:20,161
[Felix] <i>When did that guy</i>
<i>ever take a leave?</i>

400
00:26:20,245 --> 00:26:24,499
<i>We are moving on to the next stage</i>
<i>of our plans, Lara.</i>

401
00:26:25,417 --> 00:26:28,253
- Is there a problem, sir?
- You're being let in. Right now.

402
00:26:28,336 --> 00:26:29,379
[man] <i>Surrender your gun.</i>

403
00:26:29,963 --> 00:26:33,383
[Manuel, in English] <i>I hope</i>
<i>you are in the right state of mind.</i>

404
00:26:34,092 --> 00:26:35,385
- [grunts]
- Go on.

405
00:26:35,468 --> 00:26:36,303
[man] <i>Try me!</i>

406
00:26:42,475 --> 00:26:44,978
[suspenseful music playing]
